article.headline: Alabama 65, Austin Peay 47
article.story: TUSCALOOSA, Ala. (AP) -- Earnest Shelton scored 23 points and Kennedy Winston added 15 points to lead Alabama over Austin Peay 65-47 Saturday. Alabama (4-2) scored the first nine points of the game, and reached a 10 point lead when Winston hit a 3-point shot from the corner with 8:10 remaining in the first half, making it 18-18. The Crimson Tide widened its lead 38-16 after Shelton's jump shot at 3:07 and Jermareo Davidson dunk with 22 seconds left in the half. Alabama made a 7-0 run after leading 38-19 at halftime. The Tide's biggest lead was by 29 points when Shelton hit a 3-pointer with 15:34 remaining, making it 52-23. The closest Austin Peay (2-3) ever caught up in the second half was by 18 points. Adrian Henning led the Governors with a team-high 16 points and 10 rebounds and was the only player to reach double-figures. Corey Gipson added 9 points. The Tide has won all three of its meetings against Austin Peay.
